  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Church Land Programme - Core Costs Support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Until March 2017 this was considered the joint project of Christian Aid and Irish Churches funding:
CLP gives focused attention to practice and reflecting on practice, that is, to the process of animation. This has had a profound effect on the manner in which CLP approaches its work, leading to an open ended commitment to &quot;walking with communities towards the realisation of the choices that they make&quot;. CLP has thus opened itself to the politics of the poor, and its practice is guided by an active solidarity with people in the struggles that they define and take forward on their own terms. It is from the space of people&apos;s struggles that CLP is now interrogating its relationships with other stakeholders.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Until March 2017 this was considered the joint project of Christian Aid and Irish Churches funding:
CLP has embarked on a core process of animation so goals in a sense are on two levels - internal to make sure that this core practice is happening and working and on another level, that it is supporting social movements in their struggle for freedom, people who are systematically excluded and impoverished in their srtuggles in relation to land and justice. It is about how CLP can add value to the strategies and actions of social movements, how CLP can help facilitate, connect and build wider movements.
So, the goals/aims of some of the people and groups CLP work with are :
- to ensure the right of shack dwellers to speak and act for themselves in their struggle for land, housing and justice.
- to assist widows to access financial and material support from government departments and other agencies. 
- to secure livelihoods for people living on church land, or who have recently acquired church land through the land reform process.
